      "settings": {
        "tag": "HAIR BIOLOGY",
        "title": "Your Hair Growth Cycle Is Changing",
        "description": "Every hair on your head goes through a 3-phase cycle. Menopause alters the timing. Unfiltered water stresses the cycle further.",
        "menopause_title": "What Menopause Does to This Cycle",
        "water_title": "What Unfiltered Water Does to This Already Compromised Cycle",
        "timeline_title": "What to Expect: Your Results Timeline",
        "timeline_description": "Based on hair biology and customer feedback",
        "expand_title": "Deep Dive: The 8–12 Week Timeline Explained",
        "expand_text_1": "When people ask \"how long until I see results?\", the answer is rooted in hair biology. Each hair follicle cycles independently. When you remove environmental stressors, follicles in anagen begin growing healthier immediately — but you won't see the effect until that hair grows visibly.",
        "expand_text_2": "Scalp hair grows at approximately 1 cm per month. A follicle entering anagen on install day won't produce visible hair for 2–3 weeks. You need enough follicles to transition for the cumulative effect to become noticeable.",
        "expand_text_3": "This is why our 5.0 Stationary includes a 90-day guarantee and our 2.0 Handheld includes 60 days — calibrated to the biological timeline.",
        "expand_source": "Sources: Paus & Cotsarelis, 1999 (hair follicle biology) · StatPearls Hair Physiology · ScienceDirect Menopause and Hair Loss, 2025"
      }
